<subSubSection pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1437,1106,1709]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,1142,1168]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Body with numerous large, narrow, pointed spines; mid-dorsal spine anteriorly on head, mid-dorsally pair of spines on head, row of spines across pereonite 1; row of spines across pereonites 2 and 3; pereonite 4 0.2 times body length; trapezoid, about as long as second and third together; anterior and posterior rows of spines across pereonite 4, pair of spines middorsally. Pleotelson short, with several long and short spines on anterior part, one lateral spine on posterior part, posteriorly bifid apex, fork-like. Antennula short, not reaching distal end of second peduncular segment of antenna. Antenna long and slender, about 0.9 of total body length. Spines absent from basis of pereopods 5 to 7. Oostegites not present on pereopod 5.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1437,1106,1709]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,1395,1421]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Remarks:</emphasis>
The ventral lateral plate of the head has a deep incision at the anterior end of pereonite 1. The posterior end of the pleotelson ends in deep upraised fork, which distinguishes this species from all 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schultz" authorityYear="1981" box="[1217,1382,1431,1457]" class="Malacostraca" family="Arcturidae" genus="Spectrarcturus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1217,1382,1431,1457]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Spectrarcturus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, except 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stransky &amp; Svavarsson &amp; Poore &amp; Kihara" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Sars" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[289,394,1467,1493]" class="Malacostraca" family="Arcturidae" genus="Spectrarcturus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hystrix">
<emphasis box="[289,394,1467,1493]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">S. hystrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stransky &amp; Svavarsson &amp; Poore &amp; Kihara" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Benedict" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[449,583,1467,1493]" class="Malacostraca" family="Arcturidae" genus="Spectrarcturus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="murdochi">
<emphasis box="[449,583,1467,1493]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">S. murdochi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The middorsal spine on anterior part of the head can be used to distinguish this species from several other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schultz" authorityYear="1981" box="[499,664,1503,1529]" class="Malacostraca" family="Arcturidae" genus="Spectrarcturus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[499,664,1503,1529]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Spectrarcturus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1437,1106,1709]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<bibRefCitation author="Kussakin, O. G." box="[199,388,1539,1565]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" pagination="1 - 463" refId="ref19608" refString="Kussakin, O. G. (1982) Morskye I solonovatovodnye ravnonogie rakoobrasnye (Isopoda) cholodnix I umerennix vod severnogo polushariya [Marine and brackish water like-footed crustaceans (Isopoda) of cold and temperate waters of the North- ern Hemisphere]. Podotryadi Anthuridea, Microcerberidea, Valvifera, Tyloidea. Opredeliteli po Faune SSSR, Izdavaemye Zoologicheskim Institutom Akademii Nauk SSSR, 131 (2), 1 - 463. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1982">Kussakin (1982)</bibRefCitation>
noted that the specimen occurring at the Commander Island differed from the 
<typeStatus box="[1306,1404,1539,1565]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">holotype</typeStatus>
in the presence of a spine on article 3 and by having different shape of the body spines, but still considered that these specimens belonged to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Richardson" baseAuthorityYear="1899" box="[413,583,1611,1637]" class="Malacostraca" family="Antarcturidae" genus="Pleuroprion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedium">
<emphasis box="[413,583,1611,1637]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">S. intermedium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="distribution">
